        "authorId" : "57f729dd-988a-4d1a-83bf-ee70bf637c64",
        "body" : "Yeah, @alexbrand says each container in a Windows pod gets its own IP.  So containerProvidesPodIP() isn't quite the same as containerIsNetworked(), since one container is suppposed to supply the pod IP, but all of them are networked.",
